    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-25T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-25T05:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/522: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-25T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 25, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 25—9:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1416. My 983, September 1, 1 p.m.<note n="24" xml:id="d497fn24">Not
                        printed.</note> The morning papers published a DNB<note n="25"
                        xml:id="d497fn25">Deutsches Nachrichten Büro, German semi-official news
                        agency.</note> announcement to the effect that ratifications of the
                    Soviet-German Nonaggression Pact of August 23<note n="26" xml:id="d497fn26">For
                        the text of the Treaty of Nonaggression, with the secret additional
                        protocol, between Germany and the Soviet Union signed in Moscow and dated
                        August 23, 1939, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Nazi-Soviet
                            Relations, 1939–1941</hi> (Washington, 1948), p. 76.</note> were
                    exchanged yesterday in Berlin by State Secretary von Weizsäcker and the Soviet
                    Ambassador Schkwarzev.<note n="27" xml:id="d497fn27">Alexander A. Shkvartsev,
                        Soviet Ambassador to Germany from September 3, 1939.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
